SPAIN DAYBOOK: EU Leaders Meet in Brussels, Spain Cabinet Gather

-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 
2011-12-09T06:35:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/spain-daybook-eu-leaders-meet-in-brussels-spain-cabinet-gather.html
European Union leaders will today
continue a summit to negotiate measures to save the euro and
stabilize public finances in the region.  Peter Altmaier , chief whip for Chancellor Angela Merkel’s
Christian Democratic bloc in Germany’s parliament, said there’s
“no plan B” in negotiations to save the euro and warned that
failure of a European Union could damage the global economy.  ECONOMY:  *Spain’s cabinet is scheduled to meet tomorrow, followed by
news conference at around 1:30 p.m. Madrid time.  EQUITIES:  * Banco Santander SA (SAN)  may be among the active financial
stocks after Spain’s new People’s Party-led government will
decide early next year whether to create a so-called bad bank to
remove toxic assets from lenders’ balance sheets, a party
official said.  MARKETS:  *The IBEX 35 Index fell 2.12 percent to 8,461.2.  *The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing
costs widened to 380 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
